    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-16T18:14:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-16T18:14:00-05:00" n="389"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d389">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 822.00/353.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Hartman</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-16T18:00:00-05:14">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 16, 1914, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Answering your February 14, 6 p.m. The report that Tulcan is occupied by the
                    revolutionists is not true. The Minister for Foreign Affairs informed me today
                    that the Government has 10,000 soldiers and 5,000 police under arms and that it
                    is in control of all the Republic except a portion of Esmeraldas. He also said
                    that the plans of the Government at Esmeraldas are to surround the revolutionary
                    forces and capture them without bloodshed if possible. I have no way of
                    ascertaining the number of revolutionary soldiers. At present the situation is
                    favorable to the Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hartman</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
